Name: Ah Mah Homemade Cake
text: Ah Mah Homemade Cake, a well-loved best seller of castellan cakes in Malaysia, was first launched in Restoran Poh Yap, Kota Kemuning, Malaysia, on 7 April 2017. The brand and its delicious castella cakes quickly soared in popularity and within the short span of two months, opened 14 outlets across the country. Inspired by the popular egg sponge cakes originating from Tamsui (Danshui), Taiwan, Chef Jim of Ah Mah Homemade Cake has adapted traditional recipe and put a local twist on it. The cakes are freshly made every day on the spot and each batch is lovingly baked for 80 minutes.

The menu features an extensive range of donburi, ramen, nabemono,tendon, sushi and sashimi.

For you big eaters out there, double it up with the Double Up Chicken when you get to choose 2 choices of chicken.

Butterfly Peas helps protect the skin against premature aging, reduce inflammation, fight certain types of cancers and weight loss. Earl Grey Tea fights depression and prevents heart diseases. Our hot seller, My Secret Garden, a combination of three different types of flower, apple juice, soda and alluring rose buds. It is floral yet with a touch of refreshing apple juice! A drink that is popular among all age groups. Not forgetting the Milk Series! We launched the first Popcorn flavoured drink in Singapore. And we at LiHO believe that a good cup of tea topped off with our cheese will leave you surprised, delighted and wanting more.  Hence, LiHO is founded by a belief that delicious cheese tea & beverages should be available to everyone conveniently anywhere, anytime.

text: A Singapore-grown startup, MyRepublic is best known as the telco that launched Singapore and South Asia’s first 1Gbps fibre broadband plan under S$50, propelling Singapore’s internet connectivity to be ranked among the best in the world. Today, MyRepublic provides ultra-fast internet service to over 50,000 homes and businesses in Singapore. On route to bidding to be the fourth mobile operator in Singapore, expect better data plans and faster connectivity.

text: Noodles Bar by Wan Chai combines the quality and innovation of the Japanese with the comfort of old-fashioned European cuisine. We offer four types of noodles: ramen, cha soba, udon, and nissin. Diners can pair their noodles with any of the soup bases on the menu, including our signature roasted tomato basil with seafood, curry with chicken, or bonito kombu with seafood. Dry bases are also available, in the form of yakisoba and bacon aglio olio. Top your dish off with a selection of add-ons, including ponzu roast chicken and soft shell crab. Every bowl is up to your imagination

With instrumental lessons for piano, violin, vocal and guitar available, there has got to be an instrument that can help you express yourself.
